answers.answer: Hello,Odor in urine can be due to diet like coffee or asparagus, infection like bladder, prostate or urinary tract, dehydration or diabetes. You should visit your doctor for a urine examination and evaluation to find out the exact cause and treatment for the foul smell.I sincerely hope that helps. Take care.

question: For the past several months I have had a horribly strong odor to my urine.  So much that after I leave the restroom, it still smells horrible.  I have had several UTI dipstick tests from my dr and they cannot find anything wrong.  I don't eat anything unusual that would make my urine smell.  I don't have too many other symptoms other than I do urinate frequently and have an urge to go to the bathroom alot.  I don't have any pain or discharge.  What could this possibly be?
title: urine odor
